TITLE: Moldovan lawmakers approve divisive national language bill
SUMMARY: Moldovan lawmakers have voted in favor of a divisive bill that will replace references to the country’s official national language from Moldovan to Romanian in the Constitution and in legislation

TITLE: 3 dead in rioting blamed on gangs in Brazil's northeast
SUMMARY: National guard troops are patrolling northeastern Brazil after three nights of rioting allegedly ordered by imprisoned gang members that has left windows smashed, buses ablaze and at least three people dead

TITLE: Austrian police warn of abstract threat to Syrian facilities
SUMMARY: Austrian police have issued a terror threat warning for the city of Vienna, saying there was an “abstract” danger for Syrian institutions in the capital

TITLE: Credit Suisse shares soar after central bank offers lifeline
SUMMARY: Credit Suisse shares surged after the Swiss central bank agreed to loan the bank up to 50 billion francs ($54 billion) to bolster confidence in the country’s second-biggest lender following the collapse of two U.S. banks

TITLE: Strikes, protests and clashes over deadly Greek rail crash
SUMMARY: Clashes have broken out in Athens and a southern city during a general strike in Greece that drew large protests called in response to a rail disaster last month

TITLE: Israelis step up protests after Netanyahu rejects compromise
SUMMARY: Israeli protesters are pressing on with demonstrations against a contentious government plan to overhaul the judiciary

TITLE: Exhibit: 'Invisible' Monet, Leon, was key to impressionism
SUMMARY: Claude Monet’s older sibling is the focus of a landmark Paris exhibit illuminating the hitherto unknown role Leon Monet played in the French impressionist painter’s life and art

TITLE: North Korea launches ICBM before South Korea-Japan summit
SUMMARY: North Korea has test-launched an intercontinental ballistic missile hours before the leaders of South Korea and Japan meet in Tokyo at a summit expected to focus on North Korean threats

TITLE: Albania declares new national river park, backs airport plan
SUMMARY: Albania's government has formally designated the Vjosa River and its tributaries a national park, starting with an investment of some $80 million (75 million euros) to stop wastewater being poured into the river

TITLE: Netanyahu rejects judicial compromise, deepening crisis
SUMMARY: Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu has swiftly rejected a compromise proposal aimed at resolving a standoff over the future of the country’s legal system

TITLE: Blinken says Ethiopia must do more on Tigray peace deal
SUMMARY: U.S. Secretary of State Antony Blinken says Ethiopia needs to make more progress implementing a peace agreement with its northern Tigray region before relations with the U.S. are normalized

TITLE: Students call for education reform in Hungary protest march
SUMMARY: Thousands of students and other opponents of Hungary’s right-wing government have marched in the capital Budapest demanding educational reforms and a change in the Central European country’s political culture

TITLE: Mexican president floats fentanyl ban, faults US drug policy
SUMMARY: Mexico’s president is calling anti-drug policies in the U.S. a failure

TITLE: Bank fears spread to Europe, drag down shares of big lenders
SUMMARY: Battered shares of the Swiss bank lost more than one-quarter of their value.

TITLE: Iran says 110 arrested over suspected schoolgirl poisonings
SUMMARY: Iranian police say 110 suspects have been arrested in connection with the suspected poisoning of thousands of girls in schools across the country

TITLE: Austrian police: Possible threat to Vienna places of worship
SUMMARY: Austrian police are warning of a possible “Islamist-motivated attack” targeting churches and other houses of worship in Vienna

TITLE: Floods kill 14 in Turkish earthquake-battered provinces
SUMMARY: Turkish officials and media reports say floods caused by torrential rains have killed at least 14 people in two provinces that were devastated by an earthquake last month

TITLE: US and Russia ratchet up rhetoric over downing of drone
SUMMARY: Russia and the United States ratcheted up their confrontational rhetoric over a U.S. surveillance drone that encountered Russian warplanes and crashed near the Crimean Peninsula

TITLE: Award-winning South African jazz singer Gloria Bosman dies
SUMMARY: Smooth-voiced South African jazz musician Gloria Bosman has been lauded for her contribution to the country’s music industry in a career spanning more than two decades

TITLE: Neighbors Bulgaria, Romania sign agreement to boost ties
SUMMARY: Bulgarian President Rumen Radev has held talks with his visiting Romanian counterpart as the two neighbors signed a cooperation agreement to boost bilateral ties amid Russia’s ongoing war in Ukraine

TITLE: Italian court deliberates appeal of 2 US men in cop killing
SUMMARY: Italy’s highest court has started deliberations in what should be the final appeal of two U.S. citizens convicted in the stabbing death of a police officer during a plainclothes operation in Rome

TITLE: Putin, Assad discuss rebuilding Syria, regional issues
SUMMARY: Russian President Vladimir Putin has hosted Syrian leader Bashar Assad for talks in the Kremlin that focused on rebuilding Syria after a devastating civil war and efforts to stabilize the region

TITLE: Nurses, paramedics reach pay deal to end England strikes
SUMMARY: Leaders of unions representing hundreds of thousands of nurses, ambulance crews and other health care workers in England have reached a deal to resolve months of disruptive strikes for higher wages

TITLE: In Rome, church and state agree to Pantheon entrance fee
SUMMARY: Tourists in Rome checking out the Pantheon, Italy’s most-visited cultural site, will soon be charged a 5-euro ($5.28) entrance fee under an agreement between Italian culture and church officials

TITLE: Palestinians: 4 killed in Israeli army raid in West Bank
SUMMARY: Palestinian officials say an Israeli army raid has killed four Palestinians, including a teenage boy, near the occupied West Bank city of Jenin
